\frac
{
	\text{count}(1950, \text{Gary})
}
{
	\sum\limits_{y \in \text{years}} \text{count}(y, \text{Gary})
}
\end{align*}


More generally, for any name, we can compute the conditional probability mass function over birth year $B$:

	\begin{align*}
\P( B = b | N = n ) 
&\approx 
\frac
